    "title": "wallet, coin selection: config option to prioritize 'no change' when possible",
    "body": "Bitcoin Core has 3 algorithms for coin selection. All of them are executed and then, the result with the 'best' waste metric is chosen. Thinking about privacy, the user could prefer a solution that doesn't generate change (of course, users that want privacy usually prefer choose the coins manually). Anyway, what if the user could choose to prioritize the solution given by BnB? So, in the case of BnB finds a solution, the other algorithms would not need to be executed. ",
