      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "@prayank23 We have 3 algorithms in Bitcoin Core, the waste metric decides what solution should be used. So, BnB can find a solution with 10 inputs and SRD finds one with 3 inputs but generating change, if the solution provided by SRD is more economic than the BnB one, it will be choose. However, I may not want the most economic, what if I want the solution that doesn't generate change (for privacy reason)? I don't think the users should know how the algorithms work, but it would be great if he could choose a strategy. Of course, those who wanna 100% privacy will choose the coins manually, but in some cases not everyone has this possibility.\r\n\r\nThanks for posting here that other issue, I am reading it..",
